&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning and Organisational Development Analyst/Brand Designer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary:&lt;strong&gt; Band 5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours:&lt;strong&gt; 37.5 per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location:&lt;strong&gt; Learning &amp; Organisational Development, NU Building, Plymouth Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have an analytical understanding of interpreting messages from various sources of data accompanied with the ability to creatively and engagingly display information to playback and tell a story?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with a curious mind and a creative eye to join our well-established Learning and Organisational Development team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for developing a brand that complements and enhances the organisation’s education and development and cultural inquiry/ change programmes whilst owning and leading on the complex data analysis of such information. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are someone who feels comfortable multi-tasking in a busy environment and supporting in the delivery of tight deadlines, can work with a variety of people and you are looking to be part of a team striving to make a difference, we’d welcome your application for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information on this post please contact Laura Crossfield or Jayne Middleman, Learning and Organisational Development Leads via their emails at&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lcrossfield@nhs.net  or Jayne.middleman@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date:  12th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews:  w/c 30th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
